# Elixir Test Critic — Rules Reference

> **Do not edit this file directly.** Run `mix generate_toc` to regenerate.

## Quick Reference by Severity

### Critical Rules (must fix)

<%= for cat <- @categories, rule <- cat.rules, rule.severity == "critical" do %>| `<%= rule.id %>` | [<%= rule.title %>](../rules/<%= rule.category %>/<%= rule.slug %>/RULE.md) | <%= cat.name %> |
<% end %>

### Warning Rules (should fix)

<%= for cat <- @categories, rule <- cat.rules, rule.severity == "warning" do %>| `<%= rule.id %>` | [<%= rule.title %>](../rules/<%= rule.category %>/<%= rule.slug %>/RULE.md) | <%= cat.name %> |
<% end %>

---

## Rules by Category

<%= for cat <- @categories do %>
### <%= String.capitalize(cat.name) %>

<%= cat.description %>

| ID | Rule | Severity | Summary |
|----|------|----------|---------|
<%= for rule <- cat.rules do %>| `<%= rule.id %>` | [<%= rule.title %>](../rules/<%= rule.category %>/<%= rule.slug %>/RULE.md) | <%= rule.severity %> | <%= String.replace(rule.summary, "\n", " ") |> String.trim() %> |
<% end %>
<% end %>

